HEADWORD: Chick
<hw>Chick</hw> <pr>(ch⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>chykkyn</ets>, <ets>chyke</ets>, <ets>chicken</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
sprout, as seed in the ground; to vegetate.</def>
<rj><au>Chalmers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

